===Etymology 1===
From {{der|en|enm|hamme}}, from {{der|en|ang|hamm||inner or hind part of the knee, ham}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*hamō}}, {{m|gem-pro|*hammō}}, {{m|gem-pro|*hanmō}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*kanam-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*knāmā||thigh, shin}}. Cognate with Dutch {{m|nl|ham||ham}}, dialectal German {{m|de|Hamme||hind part of the knee, ham}}, dialectal {{cog|sv|ham||the hind part of the knee}}, {{cog|is|höm||the ham or haunch of a horse}}, {{cog|mga|cnáim||bone}}, {{cog|grc|κνήμη||shinbone}}. Compare {{m|en|gammon}}.

